Multimodal Annotation – Video Scene Description & Object Detection

Task Description: Review a 30-second video clip of a commercial kitchen. Provide a frame-by-frame structural annotation, identify key objects, actions, and environmental contexts.

Video Scenario: A commercial kitchen during lunch rush. A cook is chopping vegetables on a cutting board. A manager is checking a tablet with an inventory list. Two servers are plating dishes. Background noise of sizzling and chatter.

Structured Annotation Output:

Timestamp--Scene Description--Key Objects--Action--Context / Mood
00:00–00:05	Wide shot of kitchen entrance--Staff moving briskly--Stainless steel counters, hanging pans---Walking, carrying trays--High energy, fast-paced.
00:06–00:12	Medium shot of cook at prep station--Chef's knife, green bell peppers, white cutting board--Chopping vegetables (dicing motion)--Focused, repetitive task.
00:13–00:18	Close-up of manager's hands on tablet--Tablet screen (showing Excel-style grid), pen--Scrolling, tapping screen--Analytical, checking inventory levels.
00:19–00:25	Over-the-shoulder shot of servers plating--Ceramic plates, ladle, sauce pan--Plating food, garnishing--Precision, aesthetic presentation.
00:26–00:30	Return to wide shot--Staff moving in synchronized flow--None new--Passing each other, coordinated movements--Efficient, teamwork-oriented.

Quality Notes: Lighting is consistent (fluorescent overhead). No occlusion of primary subjects. Camera is stable (tripod-mounted). Audio levels are balanced with no clipping.
